This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring March 25, 2011, as "Greek Independence Day: A National Day of Celebration of Greek and American Democracy." The proclamation highlights the historical significance of Greece regaining its independence and becoming a symbol of democracy, as well as the influence of Greek culture on the United States. It emphasizes the shared values of democracy, equality, and freedom between the two countries and calls upon the American people to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.